\par }{\cf0 Apothecary
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Apothecaries are people who study the science of mixing chemicals, elements, and naturally occurring
\par materials together for predictable results. They often go on to be research scientists, inventors, pharmacists, or alchemists.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Prerequisite: }{\fs20\cf0 Age 20+.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Skills: }{\fs20\cf0 Choose three of the following skills as permanent class skills. If a skill you select is already a class skill, you receive a +1 competence bonus on
 checks using that skill. Craft (chemical, mechanical, pharmaceutical, or writing), Disable Device, Knowledge (arcane lore, earth and life sciences, history, or physical sciences), Repair, Research.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Bonus Feat: }{\fs20\cf0 Select either Arcane Skills or Educated.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Wealth Bonus: }{\fs20\cf0 +3.
\par }{\b\fs22\cf0 
\par }{\cf0 Hedge Wizard
\par }{\fs20\cf0 A hedge wizard is someone who has spent a great deal of time studying the arcane arts without the benefit of having any formal training or mentoring.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Prerequisite: }{\fs20\cf0 Intelligence 10.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Skills: }{\fs20\cf0 Choose three of the following skills as
 permanent class skills. If a skill you select is already a class skill, you receive a +1 competence bonus on checks using that skill. Concentration, Craft (chemical or writing), Decipher Script, Gather Information, Knowledge (arcane lore, art, earth and 
life sciences, history, or physical sciences), Research.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Bonus Feat: }{\fs20\cf0 Select either: Magical Heritage or Magical Affinity.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Wealth Bonus: }{\fs20\cf0 +2.
\par }{\b\fs22\cf0 
\par }{\cf0 Novitiate
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Novitiates draw quiet strength from their belief in a greater power. They do not necessarily have ties to a specific religion or denomination\emdash 
their faith is enough. Some novitiates are lay clergy, counselors, motivational speakers, social workers, or any other position involved with helping people who have lost hope and faith.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Prerequisite: }{\fs20\cf0 Wisdom 10.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Skills: }{\fs20\cf0 Choose three of the following skills as permanent class skills. If a skill you select is already a class skill, you receive a +1 competence bonus on c
hecks using that skill. Concentration, Craft (writing), Decipher Script, Diplomacy, Knowledge (arcane lore, art, behavioral sciences, history, or theology and philosophy), Sense Motive.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Bonus Feat: }{\fs20\cf0 Select either: Divine Heritage or Magical Affinity.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Wealth Bonus: }{\fs20\cf0 +2.
\par }{\b\fs22\cf0 
\par }{\cf0 Psychic
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Psychics can be people with innate, low-level psionic abilities or simply con-artists looking to make a buck off those gullible enough to believe their ruses. 
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Prerequisite: }{\fs20\cf0 Age 15+.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Skills: }{\fs20\cf0 Choose two of the following skills as perman
ent class skills. If a skill you select is already a class skill, you receive a +1 competence bonus on checks using that skill. Bluff, Concentration, Diplomacy, Gather Information, Intimidate, Knowledge (behavioral sciences, current events, popular cultur
e, or streetwise), Sense Motive.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Bonus Feat: }{\fs20\cf0 Select either Iron Will or Wild Talent.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Wealth Bonus: }{\fs20\cf0 +2.
\par }{\b\fs22\cf0 
\par }{\cf0 Shadow Scholar
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Shadow scholars fall into two categories\emdash learned Shadowkind and mundane folk who have spent time studying Shadow culture, magic, and other supernatural occurrences.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Prerequisite: }{\fs20\cf0 Age 15+.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Skills: }{\fs20\cf0 Choose three of the following skills as permanent class skills. If a skill you select is already a class skill, you receive a +1 competence bonus on checks using that skill. Decipher Script, Gather 
Information, Knowledge (arcane lore, art, behavioral sciences, earth and life sciences, history, physical sciences, tactics, or theology and philosophy), Research, or add a new Read/Write Language or a new Speak Language.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Bonus Feat: }{\fs20\cf0 Select either Arcane Skills or Educated.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Wealth Bonus: }{\fs20\cf0 +1.
\par }{\b\fs22\cf0 
\par }{\cf0 Squire
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Squires serve as assistants to warriors in hopes of learning the skills they will need to be warriors themselves one day.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Prerequisite: }{\fs20\cf0 Strength 13 or Dexterity 13.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Skills: }{\fs20\cf0 Choose three of the following skills a
s permanent class skills. If a skill you select is already a class skill, you receive a +1 competence bonus on checks using that skill. Balance, Climb, Handle Animal, Jump, Ride, Tumble.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Bonus Feat: }{\fs20\cf0 Select either Archaic Weapons Proficiency or Armor Proficiency (light).
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Wealth Bonus: }{\fs20\cf0 +1.}{\f109\fs20\cf0 
