\par }{\cf0 METAMAGIC FEATS
\par }{\fs20\cf0 As a spellcaster\rquote s knowledge of magic grows, he or she can learn to cast spells in ways s
lightly different from how the spells were originally designed or learned. For example, a spellcaster can learn to cast a spell without certain components, cast a spell for greater effect, or even cast a spell with nothing but a moment\rquote 
s thought. Altering the casting and effect of a spell is accomplished using metamagic feats.
\par Spells improved with metamagic feats use up higher-level spell slots, as noted in Table: Metamagic Spell Level Adjustments.
\par Metamagic feats cannot be used for all spells. See the specific feat descriptions for the spells that a particular feat can\rquote t modify.
