\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20\cf0 Some advanced classes must prepare their spells in advance. During preparation, members of these classes de
cide which spells to prepare with metamagic feats, remembering that any spell improved by a metamagic feat takes up a higher-level spell slot than normal.
\par Mystics cast spells at will from a limited list, as opposed to preparing them in advance. They can decide when they cast their spells whether to use metamagic feats to improve them.
\par As with other spellcasters, the improved spell uses up a higher-level spell slot. Because the Mystic has not prepared the spell in a metamagic form in advance, he must do so o
n the spot. The Mystic, therefore, must take more time to cast a metamagic spell (one improved by a metamagic feat) than a regular spell. If its normal casting time is an attack action, casting a metamagic spell is a full-round action for the Mystic. For 
spells with a longer casting time, it takes an extra full-round action to cast the spell.
\par Acolytes spontaneously casting }{\i\fs20\cf0 cure }{\fs20\cf0 or }{\i\fs20\cf0 inflict }{\fs20\cf0 spells can cast metamagic versions of them. Casting an attack action metamagic spell spontaneously is a full-round actio
n, and spells with longer casting times take an extra full-round action to cast.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Incantations: }{\fs20\cf0 An incantation cannot be the subject of a metamagic feat.
\par }\pard\plain \s5\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel4\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs20\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cf0 Effects of Metamagic Feats
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20\cf0 In all ways, a metamagic spell operates at its original spell level even tho
ugh it is prepared and cast as a higher-level spell. Saving throw modifications are not changed (unless stated otherwise in the feat description). The modifications made by these feats only apply to spells cast directly by the feat user. A spellcaster can
\rquote t use a metamagic feat to alter a spell cast from a wand, scroll, or other device.
\par }\pard\plain \s5\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel4\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs20\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cf0 Maximize Spell and Quicken Spell Abilities
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20\cf0 
Some advanced classes have special class abilities that work like metamagic feats. For example, the Maximize Spell ability of the 
Mage and the Quicken Spell ability of the Techno Mage function as metamagic feats with regard to how they interact with other metamagic feats.
\par }\pard\plain \s5\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel4\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs20\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cf0 Metamagic Magic Items
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20\cf0 A character with the Brew Potion, Scribe Scroll, or Craft Wand class ability can store a me
tamagic spell in a potion, scroll, or wand, respectively. Level limits for potions and wands apply to the spell\rquote s higher metamagic level. A character doesn\rquote t need the metamagic feat to activate an item storing a metamagic spell.
\par }\pard\plain \s5\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel4\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs20\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cf0 Multiple Metamagic Feats on a Spell
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20\cf0 A spellcaster can use multiple metamagic feats on a single spell. Changes to its level are cumulative. 
\par }\pard\plain \s5\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel4\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs20\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cf0 Counterspelling Metamagic Spells
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20\cf0 A spell enhanced by a metamagic feat does
 not affect its vulnerability to counterspelling or its ability to counterspell another spell.
\par }{\b\fs22\cf0 
\par Psionic Feats
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Some spell-related feats are equally applicable to psionics. The following psionic feats function as the named spell-related feats. Treat referenc
es to spells as powers within these descriptions, and references to caster level as manifester level.
\par }\trowd \trgaph108\trleft-108\trftsWidth1\trautofit1\trpaddl108\trpaddr108\trpaddfl3\trpaddfr3 \clvertalt\cltxlrtb\clftsWidth3\clwWidth2388 \cellx2280\clvertalt\cltxlrtb\clftsWidth3\clwWidth2610 \cellx4890\pard 
